Posted: Wed Apr 10, 2013 10:18 am
Quote:TWC 50/5 service. Shameful that YouTube/Google has switched to such a poor solutions. Months without a fix.While I agree that they need to fix it, keep in mind that YouTube has massive bandwidth requirements (between CDN servers as well as to the users), so fixing a bottleneck is not as easy as just turning on more servers. I feel like a lot of the problems are probably caused by CDN nodes put on an ISPs network to help minimize bandwidth over the peered lines, and those are almost certainly more difficult to upgrade than something entirely under Google's control.
